Hartford's "strict holding" necessarily embraces the Sherman Act's criminal applications.
^9 Indeed, properly read, American Banana contains no such suggestion.
As discussed above, the statement in American Banana on which Japan relies is itself consistent with applying the Sherman Act, civilly or criminally, to foreign conduct that produces substantial intended effects in the United States.
See supra note 3.
