See, e.g., Rhode Island v. Narragansett Indian Tribe, 19 F.3d 685, 705 (1st Cir.) cert. denied, 115 S. Ct. 298 (1994).
^11 Japan's contention that multilateral cooperation, and not the assertion of the American antitrust laws, is the proper way to address "anticompetitive acts having an international dimension," Japan Br. at 27-28, is an argument properly addressed to the Executive Branch or Congress.
